Adam Taha: Was it a heartbreak that inspired you to study about dating, or it is just out of curiosity or skill development?
Adam Taha
Artist and writer passionate about psychology of dating · Author has 5K answers and 94.4M answer views · Updated 7y ·

It was out of curiousity to learn and skills development.

As it’s part of our social life and like anything else, I don’t like doing things half heartedly. I also don’t like second guessing and have always believed, with anything in life it needs knowledge and skill.

However, it didn’t start with dating.

It started with music. I have always loved writing songs and being in the creative world. I was always trying to figure things out for the future.

Also….Arts, writing my own books in the future and figuring out how I would one day bring all my skills together into a more engaging content of music, storytelling, with illustrations and videos to solve problems..

Like getting a job, making money from your own home, getting gigs, attracting women. All sorts that I have already solved and tell it in a creative way…

As you can see it was more about a legacy for the future.

I wanted to know, how I can combine all the creativity skills to become a formidable brand within the home business. Bringing the real stuff rather than hype, get rich etc cetre.

Combining music, art, storytelling and all of it will sell my own products.

As I began working on my plan, other people heard of my work and wanted help too. They wanted practical help to bring the diamonds inside themselves in way that helps them to generate income.

Many just didn’t have the deeper understanding of sales, marketing and how to connect it all together for their own work.

Some needed direction, clarity and the know how.

Others with degrees in different professions wanted to use the Internet to attract jobs instead of just Uploading their CV’s but didn’t know where to start. It seemed complex and so I helped them from the ground up…

It lead me to become a strategic thinker and looking at the bigger picture. That my legacy isn’t about me but about helping other people to find their purpose, their direction, their purpose and show them how.

  • Whether it is overcoming that it is too late for them
  • Helping them to get back on track
  • Whether it is to find their own passion
  • Whether it is building their own business
  • To creating their own products, digital or physical
  • How to attract interest
  • To even dating

The knowledge of business, marketing, sales, phsychology, laws of success helped me to know how to do all these because I later achieved them in my life.

I had to learn many other concepts and skills.

I became passionate about life, history too in regards to sexuality…invention of modesty…the impact it had and how it came to be to socially condition society.

I became passion about learning different cultures, how things work in the world we live in, how they worked before, about people….personality traites, why things are the way they are.

I wanted concrete answers to why people say, do, avoid, buy, sell, and even put themselves in a position where their own freedom and happiness are pushed aside for acceptance, approval, validation etc cetre…

In doing so, I began to slowly and painfully invest a lot of time in documenting the process in a creative way; using all my creative skills to show the problem and and to reveal the answer in a practical rationalise structual way.

Part of the vision was to leave a legacy or a trail of knowledge for others who come after me. Like cousins, nieces, nephews and anyone else who are not part of the family too that wanted to seriously learn.

Doing so without me pushing them and like me, had to have the same desire, passion and obessession to know the answers.

So my pursuit was and still is lead by the curiousity of how things work and as I apply, as learn…make mistakes….fail…succeed…..others can see how it was done too but in a creative way.

I wanted to do it in narrative way rather than just content and one day all will be on a website to other digital platform. To also transform the knowledge into digital games that’s exciting and fun to use - and - being able to use phone, ipads etc. So all story becomes about other people than myself.

About their questions, goals, what they want to achieve, their dreams, challenges and success. I travelled the world because of this journey to meet many people who wanted to learn what I was learning.

The journey lead me to coach professionals, graduates, businesses, artists who all wanted to attract results i.e. clients, sales or opportunities. They had similar values and wondered about their legacy too.

I found I could adapt to any industry and be able to use the knowledge and skills to direct people to the destination or road to go on. It also included connecting them to the networks of experts I’ve built over the years.

People came to me because they knew I had the patience, the drive, passion, obessession to break things down, find out what works and what didn’t work, and show it in a structural, practical and creative way.

They knew I will be detailed and they knew, they had to be people who love knowledge and not complain like most do about length. They either want to learn, appreciate the knowledge or leave it alone.

They knew, I wasn’t the type who quits but will always be on this path. I had the staying emotional strength. I wasn’t doing it for acceptance. I was doing it because this is my calling. Whether people accepted or not.

That’s something I feel most don’t have. They lose focus easily, lack direction, focus and jumping from one idea to the next.

I could stay on something for years and right through completion. Some projects needed that and people saw that as strength. I didn’t think I was 20 years old, or 30 or 40 years old and I lost so much time.

I lived in the moment and believed no one knows how long we live. I could have another 50 years or one year. It doesn’t matter.

This is something powerful you can trust on and rely on in a world of shiny objects and dead link websites and people jumping different bandwagons. People regretting the past and fearing the future to lose the present.

Then I’d come back to them to explain and even do the work with people to show how it’s done with an understanding to document the process. With an understanding to be humble to learn, listen and go for it.

Word spread for people across England and other countries. They had their ideas and wanted me to be part of what they’re doing. They also had many questions I already answered so I can help share the answers.

Their self awareness is wanting.

I have lived in the real world so I had the edge.

I brought all the experiences I had with me and the strong attitude to not give a shit about social norms, customs, traditions in a way that it doesn’t stop me doing what I do. I’m very vocal about this as you’ll see in many of my answers.

I focused in building things from scratch to test what works.

Then pull them down and build them back up, testing, measuring and seeing what works. Never listening to what world says work, or experts, or coaches, or mum, dad, friends etc.

That doesn’t mean I know better but I couldn’t afford to do what most do. Thinking that someone with a degree, or status, or fame knows the answer. I had to figure it out myself or I let down many people who ask me questions.

I can’t give answers because I heard someone say that’s how it works.

I had to do the work, make the mistakes, fail, apply different ways and see the results before my very own eyes.

I knew the truth is in doing, measuring and testing because everyone has their own reality and that is their perception. I had to detach from the perception most have about life, people and success.

I wasn’t chasing the quick fix but focused on building a more stable business model that works with lifestyle and goals.

Same goes with getting jobs.

Many of my friends went and studied, got degrees but when it came to getting a job in companies they also liked, it didn’t happen. When it came to the REAL WORLD their knowledge to make things happen didn’t help them.

They believed in same value “do it all from scratch. From the ground up..”

So again, I saw this as something I’d be interested in because I could use my design, sales and marketing skills to see how it can be done. Also this is how I do things…from scratch, ground up.

I already developed a team of amazing web developers who would build what I have designed, we’d test, see what works and tweak for maximum results.

It meant I had to learn other skills like online marketing which wasn’t difficult because when you learn the foundation of human psychology, sales, marketing, advertising, copywriting…..you see it’s the same.

It’s just on a different platform and I always build from scratch.

Now how does this fit with knowledge and skills in dating?

The foundation of the knowledge for dating didn’t come from pick up artists or books on dating. I didn’t have such knowledge back then and nor did I know it existed. I didn’t even know the word “pick up artist.”

It all came from the following…

  1. Human psychology, including customer behaviour, men and women.
  2. Marketing, branding, strategy.
  3. Copywriting
  4. Advertising
  5. Sales
  6. Laws and principles of success.
  7. Lots of self development books
  8. Lots of sales and marketing training

If you look at any dating book with different phases you’ll see the same knowledge is within psychology, language of influence, marketing, sales, copywriting, self development, developing online sales process, systems, branding, strategy and on and on it gos.

For example, the first thing I ever learnt in sales is…

Invest less.

  • Identify targeted ideal prospective customers
  • Identify their desires, fears, hopes, needs and wants
  • Knowing how to harness it all into a targeted message
  • Segment different buyers
  • Screen out and filter
  • Conversion = sales

This meant I can move faster and generate more sales. I don’t have this belief that everyone is a buyer, a customer.

I don’t look at what prospects say but rather behaviour.

Notice this is the same as not looking for signals, messages but results.

I look at data where people take action i.e. subscribe, buy products, enquire etc. I don’t look for ambigious signs.

I look at how to use this data to increase increase sales while providing richer experience for clients. I don’t listen to what mainstream media says.

I don’t listen to what society says. I look at results and I’m going to know what works and what doesn’t by doing the work myself.

That’s same with dating.

I don’t ask what it means when a woman flirts, when she doesn’t call, she doesn’t text. They are irrelevant to me. They do not take action so they are not important to me. I look at women who show intent.

See how it’s not really any different.

I approach women with a strong abundant mindset that no woman is “the one.” I approach many, qualify, screen out, filter, invest less and this allows me to focus on women who are willing to invest time to date.

Anything else, I don’t give a shit about.

I don’t care what it means, why, what but her intent. The action. The result right now. I cut my time down with woman I feel are not qualified i.e. they are unwilling to invest, too slow, play hard to get etc.

I don’t care about “oh but you could lose a great woman.”

Dating isn’t like Disney.

It doesn’t happen like the Hollywood/Bollywood movies. Don’t get me started with first love and soul mate stuff promoted from decades of social conditioning.

I increased my standards and boundaries.

That doesn’t mean women I meet don’t have their standards and boundaries. It just means I know what mine are and I am approaching this way.

Companies have their own policies.

They don’t go off changing because other companies run their business in a certain way. That’s same here with dating.

I run my business my way and it’s not going to be accepted by some women. That’s fine but it hasn’t stopped me attracting women who understand, appreciate why I approach this way and they are fine about it.

You will probably see words in dating books like:

  1. Qualification process
  2. Invest less
  3. Have standards
  4. Have boundaries

In sales and marketing it’s the same

  1. Identify your customers
  2. Qualify their interest
  3. Filter, screen out.
  4. Values of your business and policies

When you know the fundamentals you can see how nothing is new.

It’s just majority of people want it now, quick rather than being patient to stop, observe, breathe and see the patterns are the same.

I would get a lot of people saying what I am saying sounds similar to different pick up artists or authors regarding dating.

That’s going to happen because the source of knowledge is the same and nothing really is new when you understand about re-branding your knowledge towards a targeted niche.

You will realise much of it is just re-packaging, with new names, new brand style, new concepts to make it look new.

It’s marketing.

It’s just changing the language towards a particular audience.

The better I got in understanding about emotions, psychology, and doing the work…the better my social instinct and conversation skills became.

With dating, I began to systematically outline a process, phases, structures for each step such as the approach, the conversation, the seduction phase.

Then I went out, applied and as I did I refined, tweaked, threw out what didn’t work, enhanced what did work. This took me some years.

I hit the streets hard, the night clubs, cafes, supermauls, wherever and at first it wasn’t easy but as time went by, I was able to put the same process of sales…marketing…and all I have learnt into dating.

I didn’t fear rejection as I have approach many people when it came to sales. I already overcome that part of social anxiety, social peer pressure, much of the myths and fallacies.

I have…lived and took many risks in life.

I went through tons of rejections but I was way past the frustrations. I approached in a fun way and I always approach dating in fun, engaging way. I don’t see dating as “approaching women” but engaging women.

I trusted the process.

What do I mean by trusting the process?

When I started years ago in sales, business, entrepreneurship…there were many social norms, customs, fallacies, myths and as time went by I overcome them. You have to be very careful when it comes to society.

People tell you their opinions and much of it is based on fears, their perception, failures and more. Some give you opinion and they never even tried what you are doing and tell you to not do it because “women don’t like to be approached.”

I don’t know how many times I heard this from women and men regarding how to not approach women who are walking, ahead of you and yet…most women I have dated happened this way.

The same myths, fallacies, misconception I found in sales, marketing, internet marketing…I found similar when it came to dating.

The second thing - I got tons of rejections in sales before I succeeded.

So I was ready for it to happen with dating, and it didn’t bother me that much. I knew it was just part of the process and need to tighten up somethings. I wasn’t counting how many rejections I had but rather what I am learning.

It was only years later that I heard of pick up artist and the many books. By that time I have begun using the internet a lot as well as social media to share what I have learnt.

I saw the knowledge that is in dating books…. closely tied to the process of human phsycology, principles of laws of success, sales, advertising and marketing.

That is why, many leave some comment that I sound like a dating expert they know, some ask if I learnt from a so, so book but the answer is no.

The source of knowledge came from sales, marketing, psychology.

So it was down to curiousity to get better at areas in my life and that also meant relationships, approaching….dating women etc.
